revision.text: {{also|Yānjīng|yǎnjìng|yǎnjīng}} ==English== {{wikipedia}} ===Etymology=== From the Pinyin romanization of {{uder|en|cmn|-}} {{zh-l|燕京|tr=Yānjīng}}, composed of [[燕]] (''Yān'', the name of one of the powers of the Warring States Period during the Zhou Dynasty) and [[京]] (''jīng'', "capital"). ===Proper noun=== {{en-proper noun}} # {{lb|en|historical}} An [[ancient]] [[city]] [[located]] within [[present-day]] [[Beijing]], the [[capital]] of [[Ji]] and [[Yan]]. # {{lb|en|informal}} An [[epithet]] of [[modern]] [[Beijing]]. # A brand of [[beer]]. [[Category:en:Beijing]]
